# GSD State Tracking

## STATE.md (always current)

`STATE.md` lives at the project root and is the memory across sessions. Update it at the **start and end of every phase**, and whenever a key decision is made or a blocker is hit.

Required fields:

```markdown
# Project State

## Current Phase
Phase 0N — <name> (in progress | complete)

## Last Task Completed
<short description>

## Next Task
<short description>

## Key Decisions
- <decision>: <rationale>

## Blockers
- <blocker or "none">
```

Create `STATE.md` if it does not exist before starting phase 01.

## Per-phase SUMMARY.md

At the end of each phase — **before merging** — create `.planning/phase-0N-SUMMARY.md`
on the phase branch. No phase is complete without its summary. Template:

```markdown
# Phase 0N — <name>

## What was built
- <bullet>

## Files changed
- <file>: <why>

## Decisions made
- <decision>: <rationale>

## Tests added
- <test file>: <what it proves>

## Known issues / follow-ups
- <item or "none">
```

## Session Start Routine

At the beginning of every session, before writing any code:

1. Read `STATE.md` to resume context.
2. Read `TECHSPEC.md` §8.2 (plan constraints) and §8.3 (Definition of Done) as
   a reminder of the workflow requirements.
3. **Print a session-start summary to the user** in this exact format:

```
## Session Resumed

- Current phase : Phase NN — <name>
- Last completed: <last task from STATE.md>
- Next task     : <next task from STATE.md>
- Branch        : feature/phase-NN-<slug>  (will create if absent)
- Spec file     : .planning/phase-NN-SPEC.md  (will create if absent)

Ready to proceed. Confirm?
```

4. **Wait for explicit user confirmation** before writing any code.
   This is non-negotiable — skipping this step was the most common failure mode.

## Spec-First Requirement

Per TECHSPEC §2.3 and §8.2: `.planning/phase-0N-SPEC.md` must exist in git
**before** any implementation code is written. If you are about to write code
and no spec has been committed, **stop** and create and commit the spec first.

## DoD Self-Check Before Phase Close

Before declaring a phase complete and merging, read TECHSPEC §8.3 and verify
every bullet is met. For test-related phases, produce a **§1.3 case verification
table** mapping each applicable test case to its test file. Any unmet criterion
blocks the merge. Only after all criteria are satisfied:

1. Commit `.planning/phase-0N-SUMMARY.md` on the phase branch.
2. Update STATE.md to "Phase NN — Complete".
3. Merge with `--no-ff` per gsd-git-workflow rule.
